npc/nadia: You made it through. But you're not in the city anymore.
npc/nadia: This is the first layer of the internet — the public web. The surface.
npc/nadia: In the real world, it looks like a screen full of apps and bright promises. In here, you see it for what it is.
npc/nadia: Those swarming things? We call them Adbots — spam given a body. Automated. Endless. They flood every corner of this place.
npc/nadia: They were designed after the gambling ads that started this whole crisis. Same psychology. Same flashing patterns. But faster, and multiplied across millions of devices.
npc/nadia: Don't trust anything that flashes and makes promises. That's how the trap works — out there AND in here.
npc/nadia: The signal we're tracing goes deeper. Much deeper than this layer.
npc/nadia: Keep moving.
npc/nadia: One more thing before you go — watch the platforms here.
npc/nadia: Some of them are baited. They glitter with easy coins, a free foothold right where you want one. Step on, grab the coin, and it bites — slows you, drains you, or flips your controls.
npc/nadia: That is exactly how they got me. "Just claim your free credit." I claimed it. Then the next, and the next, until my rent money was gone and I was still chasing the first free thing.
npc/nadia: Nothing here is free. If a platform looks too generous, it is not a gift. It is bait.
